## Anthropic — Messages

**Path**: `POST /v1/messages`

**Example base URL**: `https://api.nanobridge.net/anthropic`

On the OpenAI host you can also call `POST /anthropic/v1/messages` (full URL: `https://api.nanobridge.net/anthropic/v1/messages`).

The gateway speaks Anthropic Messages on the wire and translates to upstream Chat Completions internally.

**Auth**: `Authorization: Bearer <API_KEY>` or `X-Api-Key: <API_KEY>`

### Common request fields

| Field | Type | Description |
|-------|------|-------------|
| `model` | string | Model ID; recommended `deepseek-v4-flash` |
| `messages` | array | Messages (required); `system` may be a separate field or inside `messages` |
| `max_tokens` | integer | Max reply length (required by most Anthropic clients) |
| `stream` | boolean | Enable streaming; default `false` |

With `stream: true`, the response is Anthropic-style `text/event-stream` (SSE).

### cURL

```bash
curl https://api.nanobridge.net/anthropic/v1/messages \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -H "Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY" \
  -d '{
    "model": "deepseek-v4-flash",
    "max_tokens": 1024,
    "messages": [{"role": "user", "content": "Hello!"}]
  }'
```

